As of the 2010 census, there were 94 people living in the CDP: 43 male and 51 female. 37 were 19 years old or younger, 20 were ages 20–34, 17 were between the ages of 35 and 49, 9 were between 50 and 64, and the remaining 11 were aged 65 and above. The median age was 30.0 years.

The racial makeup of the CDP was 94.7% [[Race (United States Census)|American Indian]], 3.2% [[Race (United States Census)|Asian]], 1.1% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], and 5.3% [[Race (United States Census)|two or more races]].  12.8% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.

There were 28 households in the CDP, 20 family households (71.4%) and 8 non-family households (28.6%), with an average household size of 3.36. Of the family households, 10 were married couples living together, 8 were single mothers, and 2 w3ere single fathers; the non-family households included 8 adults living alone: 3 male and 5 female.

The CDP contained 41 housing units, of which 28 were occupied and 13 were vacant.<ref name=GR2>{{cite web |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0431182 |title=American FactFinder: Hard Rock CDP, Arizona |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=November 23, 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213062844/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0431182 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 }}</ref>

